properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued January 21 at 2:38PM PST until January 23 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Combined seas 15 to 17 feet tonight subsiding to 10 to 13
feet Wednesday. Bar conditions severe tonight becoming rough
Wednesday..

* WHERE...Grays Harbor Bar.

* WHEN...Until 4 AM PST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft
especially when navigating in or near harbor entrances.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Maximum ebb currents will occur around 230
AM and 245 PM Wednesday. The afternoon ebb will be strong.
properties.instruction:
A Small Craft Advisory for rough bar means that wave conditions
are expected to be hazardous to small craft in or near harbor
entrances.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 AM PST THURSDAY
